mplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Ehcache DefaultTransactionManagerLookup explicitly discovers Bitronix via bitronix.tm.TransactionManagerServices, and existing reachability metadata covers Bitronix resource registration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix references javax.jms from an optional dependency that is not pulled transitively; native/JVM analysis of BTM resource classes can otherwise encounter missing JMS API types.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck=true before creating CacheManager/Cache instances, or use an Ehcache configuration with updateCheck=false, to avoid the built-in network update checker. If exercising Bitronix lookup, create a temp bitronix.properties with bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true and bitronix.tm.journal=null, set bitronix.tm.configuration to it for the test, then shut down TransactionManagerServices and clear the property afterward.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Ehcache 2.5.0 adds memory-size/SizeOf code that may try agent, Unsafe, or reflective sizing; tests that use maxBytesLocalHeap or size-of internals are more native-image-sensitive and need local Gradle/native verification.\",\n    \"Bitronix keeps process-global transaction manager state; tests must clean it up to avoid order-dependent failures.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f2572aabab88364016a42fb116638819095a1e97d5e18b06a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2254, "output": 1398, "cacheRead": 51712, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55364, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782774530348, "responseId": "resp_0f2572aabab88364016a42fb0372208190b459e02f995ef7e4"}}
